      "writtenOn": "2020-07-31T16:24:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Although this is bikeshedding I\u0027d like to decide here what convention we want to use for describing tests, e.g. do we want to capitalize the descriptions?\n\nIn some places, the outer Convey is a general description of a test suite, and the inner conveys are full descriptions of specific scenarios, e.g. https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/milo/common/config_test.go\n\nIn other places, the outer Convey is a subject and the inner Convey are predicates, like what we have here, and in https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/dm/appengine/model/execution_test.go.\n\nI think what you\u0027ve written is good; for the outer Convey though would we rather use the literal function name, (e.g. \"NormalizeKey\", \"ParseFooter\", or some description noun phrase like \"Key normalization\", \"Footer parsing\"? What do you think?",
      "range": {
